article.description: Justin James scored 23 points and grabbed seven rebounds and Wyoming edged Grambling 86-78 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: James with 23 points leads Wyoming over Grambling 86-78
article.linkText: James with 23 points leads Wyoming over Grambling 86-78
article.story: LARAMIE, Wyo. -- Justin James scored 23 points and grabbed seven rebounds and Wyoming edged Grambling 86-78 on Wednesday night. Hunter Maldonado added 21 points and a team-high 12 rebounds for the Cowboys (1-2). Trevon Taylor scored 21 points off the bench and contributed seven rebounds and Jake Hendricks chipped in 13 points. Wyoming had 10 team steals contributing to 15 Grambling turnovers. Taylor's 3-pointer early in the first half gave the Cowboys a lead they would not relinquish and a Hendricks 3 later in the half made it 31-21. Wyoming was up 52-52 at the break. Grambling trailed throughout the second half -- and starters Devante Jackson and Zavier Peart both fouled out -- but Anthony Gaston drained two 3-pointers in the final four minutes to help cut it to 84-76 with 1:22 left. Dallas Polk-Hillard scored 14 points with five rebounds for the Tigers (1-1). Axel Mpoyo added 13 points.
